        <definition>spi_operation_t spi_config::operation</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>operation</name>
        <qualifiedname>spi_config::operation</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Operation flags. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>It is a bit field with the following parts:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>0: Master or slave.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>1..3: Clock polarity, phase and loop mode.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>4: LSB or MSB first.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>5..10: Size of a data frame (word) in bits.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>11: Full/half duplex.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>12: Hold on the CS line if possible.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>13: Keep resource locked for the caller.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>14: Active high CS logic.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>15: Motorola or TI frame format (optional).</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>If <computeroutput>CONFIG_SPI_EXTENDED_MODES</computeroutput> is enabled:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>16..17: MISO lines (Single/Dual/Quad/Octal).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>18..31: Reserved for future use. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
